The economic effect of Covid-19 has filtered through to the job market with a number of firms planning to retrench workers. Unions, however, do not think this is the way to go, and Fedusa has called for a moratorium on all layoffs in an effort to preserve jobs. Business Day TV spoke to Fedusa general secretary Riefdah Amaj. Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Pocket Casts | Player.fm